name: plunk
desc: Sirch is a quick AngularJS application demonstrating a few concepts that I have found helpful in creating Plunker.
longDesc:
# Sirch

Sirch is a quick AngularJS application demonstrating a few concepts that I have found helpful in creating Plunker.

### Transpiling

* The code is written in Coffee-Script but is compiled and served by Plunker transparently as Javascript
* This html partial is in fact written in Markdown and is also compiled and served by Plunker transparently, but this time as HTML

### AnguarJS pushState routing

This demo uses Angular's powerful pushState routing to allow users to use the back button as if full page reloads were happening.

### Custom data source in AngularJS

If you look at the way the twitter search results are implemented, you will see that a novel technique is used to provide re-usable, refreshable
results.

### Using resolve to ensure async resources are loaded before display

Route partials are not rendered until all required `resolve` promises have resolved.  This means there is a possible lag
while both the partial and any required ajax requests are completed.  To help the user understand this, an overlay is used.

The overlay watches for `$routeChangeStart`, `$routeChangeSuccess` and `$routeChangeError` to allow it to display and hide itself
while a route change is in progress.
